{% extends "base.jinja" %}
{% block title %}Home{% endblock %}
{% block content %}

<div class="hero">
  <h1>Amphib 🐸</h1>
  <p class="sub">Amphib ingests a resume PDF, extracts structured data with an LLM, cross-references GitHub for ground truth, and produces an explainable score.</p>
  <div class="hero-badges">
    <img alt="Python" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11%2B-blue.svg">
    <img alt="License: MIT" src="https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-yellow.svg">
  </div>
</div>

<div class="features">
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">📄</span>
    <h3>PDF Parsing</h3>
    <p>Converts resume PDFs to clean Markdown while preserving structure — headings, links, tables, all intact.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">🧠</span>
    <h3>LLM Extraction</h3>
    <p>Section-by-section extraction using Jinja-templated prompts. Works with Ollama (local) or Gemini.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">🐙</span>
    <h3>GitHub Enrichment</h3>
    <p>Fetches real profile and repo data, classifies projects, and picks the most meaningful contributions.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">📊</span>
    <h3>Fair Scoring</h3>
    <p>Objective evaluation across four axes with evidence, bonus points, and deductions — no black boxes.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">🔒</span>
    <h3>Offline-First</h3>
    <p>Run fully local with Ollama. Your data never leaves your machine unless you choose Gemini.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature-card">
    <span class="emoji">📦</span>
    <h3>CSV Export</h3>
    <p>Development mode caches results and appends to a CSV for batch analysis and iteration.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Quick start</h2>

<pre><code>git clone &lt;your-repo-url&gt; && cd amphib
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
ollama pull gemma3:4b
cp .env.example .env
python score.py resume.pdf</code></pre>

<p>See the <a href="setup.html">Setup guide</a> for detailed instructions.</p>

<h2>Why Amphib?</h2>

<p>Because it lives in two worlds — the structured world of resumes and the messy reality of GitHub — and it's comfortable in both.</p>

{% endblock %}
